---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '@components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Meet Crystal — Founder of ChevyRoots"
  description="Crystal is the founder of ChevyRoots. She drives a Silverado ZR2, attends car shows across the country, and writes every week about the trucks and cars she actually loves. This is her story."
  ogImage="/photos/crystal/crystal-silverado-zr2-hero.jpg"
>
  <section class="crystal-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="crystal-hero-grid">
        <div class="crystal-hero-image" role="img" aria-label="Crystal with her Silverado ZR2"></div>
        <div class="crystal-hero-text">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">Founder · Editor in Chief</p>
          <h1 class="crystal-hero-title">Crystal</h1>
          <span class="gold-line"></span>
          <p class="crystal-hero-tag">Run by a Chevy Girl. Driven by one, too.</p>
          <p class="crystal-hero-body">
            I'm Crystal — I grew up around Chevys, drive a Silverado ZR2 now, and started ChevyRoots because I couldn't find a single Chevy website that wasn't either a dealer lead-gen farm or an AI-generated spec sheet mill. There wasn't a place telling the real story of these trucks and cars from someone who actually owns one and shows up to the events. So I built it.
          </p>
          <div class="crystal-hero-ctas">
            <a href="/crystals-corner/" class="btn btn-gold">Read the Column</a>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline">Say Hi</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="crystal-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>The Truck</h2>
      <p>My current ride is a <strong>Silverado ZR2</strong> — the off-road trim, not a base work truck. I chose it over the TrailBoss because I wanted the factory skid plates, Multimatic DSSV shocks, and the front and rear lockers. It's the truck I actually off-road in, daily-drive, take to events, and write about honestly.</p>
      <p>Every Silverado article on this site — warranty breakdowns, mod reviews, long-term ownership takes, maintenance walkthroughs — is written from the perspective of someone who drives the exact truck being discussed. That's not marketing. That's just how the site works.</p>

      <h2>What I Do Here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Crystal's Corner</strong> — my weekly editorial column. What I saw, what I drove, what I think about a specific thing in the Chevy world that week.</li>
        <li><strong>Event reports</strong> — I attend around one major car show every two weeks. Goodguys, local cruise nights, SEMA, Bowtie Nationals. Every show becomes a photo/video/writeup package on the site.</li>
        <li><strong>Video content</strong> — in-car POV, driving videos, walk-arounds of cool builds at shows, occasional dealer walk-ins where I talk through what I'm looking for.</li>
        <li><strong>The face of the partnerships</strong> — dealerships, brands, event organizers, and tourism boards all deal directly with me.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Independent Matters</h2>
      <p>Most "Chevy" content online is written by people who don't own the vehicles they're writing about. It's either SEO content farms, manufacturer press-release rewrites, or dealer-paid articles that pretend to be objective reviews. None of that is the truth about what it's like to actually own and love these machines.</p>
      <p>ChevyRoots is different because I'm different: I own Chevys, I go to shows, I talk to other owners, and when something about a truck is annoying I say so, even if it's my own. Nobody pays me to say nice things. Sponsored content on this site — when it exists — is always clearly labeled.</p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>If you're a dealership in a major metro, a brand with an actual Chevy-relevant product, an event organizer who wants real coverage, or a journalist writing about women in the Chevy community — email me directly at <a href="mailto:hello@chevyroots.com">hello@chevyroots.com</a>. I respond personally to partnership inquiries.</p>
      <p>If you're an enthusiast who wants to share a build, tip me off to an event, or just say hi — same email. The inbox is open.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <NewsletterCTA source="crystal-bio" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .crystal-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 60px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--charcoal) 0%, #1f1a0e 50%, var(--charcoal) 100%);
  }
  .crystal-hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.3fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .crystal-hero-image {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    background: #222 url('/photos/crystal/crystal-silverado-zr2-hero.jpg') center / cover no-repeat;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }
  .crystal-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 0.9;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--off-white);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .crystal-hero-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .crystal-hero-body {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .crystal-hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .crystal-section {
    padding: var(--section-pad) 0;
  }
  .crystal-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    color: var(--off-white);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--gold);
  }
  .crystal-section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .crystal-section p {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .crystal-section strong { color: var(--off-white); }
  .crystal-section a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: underline; }
  .crystal-section ul {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    list-style: disc;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .crystal-section li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .crystal-hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
